						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Base of the Vināyaka image set up on the roof of the maṇḍapa in the Amṛitēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>12th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record states that the image was got prepared by Mallaṇṇa and Nākimayya, son of Dhuṇḍadēva described as the son of the Thousand <hi rend="italic">Sameya</hi> who were the <hi rend="italic">dēvaputrakas</hi> of god Amṛitēśvara of <hi rend="bold">Aṇṇigere.</hi> In characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th Century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
